<div> </div>
<!--start left column-->
<div class="g9">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>Chalet Hotels offer a relaxed, informal atmosphere, with professional service from your Chalet Hotel Manager and our team of chefs and hosts. All have a comfortable lounge and a residents-only bar, the ideal place for a refreshing beer after a long walk, or a quiet post-dinner drink, and many also have additional facilities such as a sauna, swimming pool or sun-terrace.</strong></p>
<p><strong><a name="Plus"></a>Half-Board PLUS Chalet Hotel Meals</strong></p>
<p><strong>Breakfast (daily)</strong> - A buffet breakfast including a choice of cereals, fruit juices, local breads, cold meats, cheeses and preserves with tea &amp; coffee, plus a hot ‘dish of the day’ six days per week, such as pancakes, sausage or bacon, which is freshly cooked to order.</p>
<p><strong>Packed Lunch (5 days a week)</strong> Packed up before you leave for the day, this generally includes a filled roll, crisps, a drink, fruit and a snack bar, to keep you going until your return home.</p>
<p><strong>Afternoon Tea/Coffee &amp; Cake (5 days a week)</strong> After a day’s walking or exploring, return to a well earned ‘cuppa’ and a slice of freshly baked home-made cake.</p>
<strong>‘Culinary Choice’ Dinner</strong> Our Chalet Hotels make the evening meal a highlight of the day, with our 5 course menus served five days a week, accompanied by a choice of free quality wines. We offer choices for each course and ask that you make your selection at breakfast each day, so that our chef’s team can prepare everything fresh for you that evening. Meals can be as sociable or as private as you wish, with larger tables for groups of friends, whether old or new, or private tables for more intimate dining. Barbecue/Al Fresco Evening In addition, one night each week, weather permitting, we will eat outdoors with a more informal menu.</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Our Chalet Hotels</h2>
<p>We have 3 fantastic Chalet Hotels across Austria, Italy and France, each with their own unique style and offering you access to some of the most breathtaking scenery in the European Lakes &amp; Mountains.</p>
<div class="data-grid" style="float: center;">
